In this article, the White House Press Secretary states that Congress has two options: either pay the bills they have accumulated or risk putting the nation into default. The statement expresses encouragement that Congressional Republicans may reconsider their demand for drastic cuts in Medicare, education, and programs that middle-class families rely on. The article emphasizes the urgency for Congress to pay its bills and pass a clean debt limit increase promptly. Additionally, the President is committed to reducing the deficit in a balanced manner.